{
  "texts": [
    "Ostracods inhabit both marine and freshwater environments, and their fossils are used to infer past environmental conditions, such as salinity and water depth (Anadón et al. 2002).",
    "The preservation of their calcified shells allows for detailed environmental reconstructions.",
    "• Radiolarians and Diatoms: Radiolarians are single-celled marine protists with intricate silica skeletons, while diatoms are algae with silica cell walls.",
    "Both groups are significant for studying past ocean productivity and environmental conditions.",
    "Their silica-based structures are well-preserved in sedimentary rocks, making them of utility to marine biostratigraphy (Okosun and Osterloff 2014)."
  ]
}